cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper is about a computer vision task that involves localizing and describing salient regions in images in natural language. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel architecture for this task, which involves a recurrent neural network language model, so it is also likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on a large dataset of images and captions, so it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
